Universities admit people of all classes and walks of life.They also create wealth, mostly through tax incomes, and are thus seen as motors of economic development. Our universities need adequate reforms to make them stay afloat. They play an important role in the pursuant of socio-economic development and democratic agenda for any country.
They have been central in addressing inequality by opening doors to previously marginalised and under-represented groups of society, including women, children and older persons access higher education. 



