Universities admit people of all classes and walks of life. They also create wealth, mostly through tax incomes, and are thus seen as motors of economic development.
The challenge has been the fact that investment in universities takes a while to realise returns. This is where there is need for public reforms and leadership to make these entities play their rightful role in development. 
Deregulation of fees
Public sector reforms, which have been recommended for a long time, should have a bearing on higher education as well.



